Put oven rack in upper third of oven and preheat oven to 400Â°F. Stir together tomatoes, brown sugar, mustard, and salt in a bowl. Gently stir in beans and transfer to a 2-quart shallow baking dish. Arrange onion slices in 1 layer over beans, then cover onion with bacon. Bake, uncovered, until bacon is browned and beans have absorbed most of liquid, about 1 1/4 hours.